 Port Elizabeth - Contrary to common belief, wills are not only for the rich and wealthy. Anyone with some property and personal belongings that will remain behind when they pass on musthave a will. A will is an essential part of a person's estate plan. It is the primary document for transferring your assets upon your death. So, why do you need a will? Contact Bardine Hall at Goldberg & de Villiers Inc on 041 501 9800 to assist you to draft a will that meets your needs and wishes. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. 